replies.body:
I disagree.  As someone who can confidently say hates assassins just as much as anyone, I always felt Ahri was the healthiest assassin in the game.  That is, when she used to be one before the rework.  She had a distinct reliance on a slow skillshot to receive her damage amp which could be clearly itemized against.

{{item:3140}} 

Now Ahri lacks any real identity other than as a crutch for low-skilled players to compensate for their own badness.  They removed most of the skill from her kit, added a little bit of safety and then removed a lot of damage, range and sustain after because(surprise surprise) her current kit is designed to prevent punishing bronzies for being bronze.
